HEADWORD: Sinistrin
<hw>Sin"is*trin</hw> <pr>(s⟦icr⟧n"⟦icr⟧s*tr⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>sinister</ets> left.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
mucilaginous carbohydrate, resembling achroodextrin, extracted from
squill as a colorless amorphous substance; -- so called because it is
levorotatory.</def>⟦br⟧
